body_text.text: The Image Group slice is what you're looking for if you want to place images in the body of your article.
Important Things to Know

Since there's only one image in this group, it will take up the full width of the article.
If you would like to place an image that is the full width of the page, please use the Full Width Image slice.
Two 16:10 Images

The cropping option when you hover over a selected image. In the cropping tool, you can dictate the desired aspect ration by changing the pixel width and height of the image, as well as the portion of the image that you'd like to display (the crop).
Need help calculating the pixel widths and heights needed for a specific ratio?
Visit this aspect ratio calculator
Set Common Preset to Custom
Input your desire Ratio Height and Ratio Width
Plug in one of the current height or width values.
